Tic-Tac-Toe Game

Description
This Tic-Tac-Toe game is a Java application that allows two players to play the classic game of Tic-Tac-Toe on a graphical user interface. The game features alternating turns between 'X' and 'O', visual indication of the current player's turn, and automatic detection of winning conditions.

Features
Graphical User Interface (GUI): Built using Swing components for buttons, labels, and panels.
Turn-Based Gameplay: Players take turns to place 'X' or 'O' on a 3x3 grid of buttons.
Winning Condition Detection: Automatically detects when a player achieves three in a row horizontally, vertically, or diagonally.
Game Outcome Display: Displays "X wins" or "O wins" when a player achieves three in a row.
Random Player Start: The game randomly determines which player starts first.

How to Play
Run the Main class (Game) to start the Tic-Tac-Toe game.
The game randomly selects which player ('X' or 'O') starts first.
Click on any of the 3x3 grid buttons to place your marker ('X' or 'O').
The game alternates turns between 'X' and 'O'.
The game automatically checks for winning conditions after each move.
If a player achieves three in a row, the game announces the winner and disables further gameplay.
To start a new game, close the application and rerun the Main class.

Contributions
Contributions to enhance the game's functionality (e.g., adding AI opponent, improving UI/UX, adding sound effects) or fixing bugs are welcome. Please fork the repository and create a pull request.
